Project: Microsoft Azure

Overview

In the prj-data-azure project, I led the design and implementation of a Data Lake architecture on Microsoft Azure, based on Raw, Enriched, and Curated layers (Medallion Model). I designed ingestion pipelines with Azure Data Factory and Databricks, optimizing data loading into Azure Data Lake Storage Gen2. I applied scalable transformations using Spark and Delta Lake to ensure ACID compliance and versioning, and orchestrated automated ETL/ELT workflows. Additionally, I defined partitioning schemes, security policies, and continuous monitoring to maintain the solutions integrity, traceability, and high performance.

Project: Azure Databricks

Overview

In the prj-data-databricks project, I led the design and implementation of a Lakehouse on Azure Databricks, structured in BronzeSilverGold layers. I automated the ingestion of alerts from an external API using Python notebooks and Databricks Jobs, storing them in Delta Lake with optimized partitioning. In the Bronze layer, I captured raw data; in Silver, I applied transformations, cleansing, and enrichment with Spark SQL; and in Gold, I built tables optimized for analytical consumption. I orchestrated workflows with Databricks Workflows, managed versioning with Unity Catalog, and established security policies and continuous monitoring to ensure performance and governance.

Project Structure

1. Bronze Layer

  • Stores the downloaded unprocessed files in JSON format.
  • Notebook:
    • 00-download_jsonfiles_alerts
    • 00_download_jsonfile_investigations

2. Silver Layer

  • Performs the initial data transformation, extracting relevant information.
  • Structuring and cleaning data into intermediate tables.
  • Tables:
    • 01-ingest_json_alerts_tb
    • 01_ingest_json_investigations_tables

3. Gold Layer

  • Contains processed data ready for analytical consumption.
  • Tables:
    • 02_ingest_join_alert_investigations_tables

4. Utilities

  • Contains reusable functions and scripts for data ingestion and transformation.
  • Folder: src/utils

Use Cases

  • Automated ingestion of alerts from an API such as EMVO.
  • Transformation and storage of data in Databricks for advanced analytics.
  • Integration with dashboards or reports to visualize trends and patterns in alerts.

Project in Microsoft Fabric

This project represents a workflow in Microsoft Fabric for data management and processing in a Lakehouse, from ingestion through to visualization in reporting tools.

Project Structure

Data Source

Data is ingested from two main sources:

  • API: An external data source based on web services.
  • Data Lake Storage: Cloud storage where raw/unprocessed data is kept.

Ingestion

  • dwflow_ingest_data: An automated process (likely Dataflows Gen2) that extracts data from the API and the Data Lake Storage.
  • pl_df_Ingest_data: Likely represents a data pipeline in Data Factory or Synapse Dataflows that processes and standardizes the data before landing it in the Lakehouse.

Transform & Storage

  • Lakehouse_LK1: Represents a Lakehouse in Microsoft Fabric, where structured and semi-structured data is stored.
  • nb_transform_data & dwflow_transform: Notebooks (probably using Spark/PySpark) and Dataflows used to perform data transformations within the Lakehouse.

Reporting and Visualization

The transformed data in the Lakehouse is consumed by Power BI or other visualization platforms to produce reports and enable analysis.

Pipeline Deployment (DevOps)

I deploy pipelines in Azure DevOps for source integration and their continuous delivery.
